# Blokko - Pattern Match & Clear Game

## Project Overview
Blokko is a strategic puzzle-matching game where players must clear blocks by matching them according to specific templates. The game features different board sizes (6x6 and 8x8), multiple levels, and various game mechanics.

## Core Game Mechanics
- Players select two adjacent blocks (horizontally or vertically)
- Match these blocks with one of four templates shown at the bottom
- Matched blocks are permanently removed (no refilling)
- Win by clearing all blocks; lose when no more valid matches are possible

## Design Guidelines
- Use the defined color palette:
  - Deep Space Gray (`#333945`) - Main background
  - Light Elegant Gray (`#F5F7FA`) - Secondary UI elements
  - Moon White (`#E8EAF6`) - Main text on dark backgrounds
  - Graphite Gray (`#5C6B73`) - Secondary text
  - Mint Green (`#76D7C4`) - Accent color for buttons, selections
- Block colors:
  - Coral Pink (`#F1948A`)
  - Sunny Yellow (`#F7DC6F`)
  - Sky Blue (`#85C1E9`)
  - Grape Purple (`#BB8FCE`)
  - Jade Green (`#7DCEA0`)
  - Terracotta Orange (`#E59866`)

## Technical Constraints
- Use setState for state management (no complex state management libraries)
- Use shared_preferences for data storage
- No external assets/images required
- No external fonts required
- No account functionality needed
- No network image caching required